There are a few homeless like everywhere, however the owner hears gets along with quite a few of them and they come from off the railroad tracks. The ones we have around here have jobs. It's nice to say hi to them, most of them around this location are clean. In fact the last three group s had to move not because the city but the railroad company. This new group picks up their stuff and paper and trash. So the railroad and the city are leaving them alone. Great store and it's more of a market than a liquor store. They do have liquor. <rate>5<//rate><text>Went here in March 2017, it was a blast! They have some nice facilities like a cafeteria, a swimming pool and a small telescope observatory that we used at night.  The zip line was fun and super exhilarating. The scenery is gorgeous with rolling mountains covered in scraggly little pine trees that you see in the high desert. <user>109377867656628844148< /user>< resp>
None< /resp>
< Text>
I went in July, and it was a great experience.  Simply one of the best 1 week camps around.  Pool, rifles, archery, and even laser tag!  Other events include biplane, low ropes, high ropes, box forts, free time, canoeing,  nature hike, treasure hunt, and fun zone, which includes gaga ball, chess, foosball, and ping pong.  I was placed with Becker and Chance, great counselors, Every night, you sing songs, and also every evening there is an event.  On Saturday, its the amazing race, on Sunday, its the Watermelon social, on Monday, its movie night, on Tuesday, its the Color Run and Ice cream social,   On Wednesday, its the dance, on Thursday, its the counselor hunt, and on Friday, there is a penny exchange.  The food is enchiladas, chicken, rice, tacos, etc. for lunch and dinner, and breakfast is bacon, toast, eggs, and orange juice.  There are punishments for dirty cabins, and on Wednesday is a team day.  The buses are good, and you can watch movies in the bus.  I would definitely recommend this place to anyone.< /Text>

< rating>
5< /rating>
< Text>
Great place for retreats, drive up is very scenic. Stop along the way  in Mentone at 5 he A&W for a true root beer float. Also take  your time once you enter in to mountains.  This is mostly a two lane road. There are plenty of places to stop and see some spectacular Vistas of the local mountains do bring your cameras.
The camp is self is very well maintained,  and offers a variety of things to do as fun activities and team building experiences.
From weekend to week long they offer programs that one fit your needs.
The property and cabins are well maintained, the food is good and the area is  picturesque.
They have added some amenities to heighten the experience,  Zip line rides over the lake. .overall great experience.</Text>

<Rate>3< /Rate>< text>
I have used Chem Dry for several years. We try to clean our carpets about every 6 to8 months. The Chem Dry company that we had used previously went bankrupt and Integrity took over their clients. This was the first time we used Integrity. The serviceman did an excellent job of cleaning the carpet. It’s just my wife and I and the carpet is only in the 4 bedrooms so it doesn’t get tremendous traffic and doesn’t really get very dirty.

But my disappointment is that it normally takes about 4 hours or so for the carpet to dry. This time it took over 2 days. They were cleaned onThursday around 11:00am. Here it is Saturday morning around 10:20am and they are finally drying out. They are a little damp but we now feel comfortable walking on them. We actually had to cancel our cleaning service on Friday. We spent a lot of time on Friday using big towels to try to absorb the moisture.

One of the reasons we started using Chem Dry is because they don’t use a lot of water so the  carpet and padding don’t  get soaked. One of our concerns has always been that when they get soaked, mildew can develop and cause the carpet to retain a musty odor. We don’t smell anything yet and hope that none develops.

I am not sure what happened this time but I think it’s important to bring this to your attention so that it can be corrected going forward. ☹️<//text>

< Review>
My husband and I have been getting tattooed by Reed for over 1 1/2 years now. He is talented, creative, knowledgeable and friendly. He and his wife Nerissa (who does all the piercings and is also equally awesome) own the shop and have been there for over 15 years. They have become friends and we couldn’t be happier with all of the work we’ve had done. Greg also tattoos in this shop and does a great job as well. Reed and Greg do different styles so between the two of them, they really do cover a large amount of styles. Really can’t go wrong with either one for tattoo work. If you’re looking to get quality work done, this is the place to go! We get so many compliments on our tattoos and always tell our tattoo admirers about Lake Monster!</Review>

<Review>Have shoppped here for years-closest convenience store in NW Highland Park, on Ave  64. with safe parking (unlike Figuroa.) Family run by hardest working, best cashiers and business people I have encountered anywhere.  Great selection of craft beers and pop, along with classic liquor, and enough food and produce for local residents with limited transportation to buy a healthy meal.  Fair prices, lucky lotto, and genuine personal service.</Review>< username>

Thai Specialty is an amazing restaurant.  If your a Thai die hard you won't be disappointed. If your a new Comer and are thinking about it. This is the place for you. The friendly staff will help you navigate the menu. The yellow chicken currie with cashews added is my favorite. If your on the fence hop off it and come in for dinner.  You'll thank me later< /Text>
<pics>None</pics></record></dataset><record>
<Rate>4</Rate><Resp>None</Resp><name>Moriah M<//name>< review>
LARGE portion of (Tofu Veggie) Pad Thai & big summer rolls.

I didn’t eat it until about 30 min after pick up, so the noodles were a little stuck together but they came apart easily after mixing it.
Personally, I would’ve liked more green onions and vegetables but that’s just my preference.
Lacks a little flavor but it’s good overall. I forgot to ask for chili paste when I picked up my food, but luckily I have some at home.

Probably wouldn’t get the summer rolls again though. They’re HUGE, but not flavorful enough for me

4 ⭐️‘s because for $10.99 this is a fairly large portion of pad thai< /review>

<gmap_id>0x80dcd456ed5313b9:0x2f7e04785c2c9c8b<//gmap_id>< review>
Normally it's an excellent restaurant, the food is consistently good and obviously great quality. The reason for the average rating comes from my most recent experience. Hours state closing is at 10. So food should be served until 10. However I understand the kitchen needs to be cleaned and people want to go home, so having the kitchen stop taking orders at 9:45 or even 9:30 is understandable.
I've gone several times just before 9:30 and ordered something Togo without issue.

Tonight I ask for a Togo order at 921 and was told no, that though store hours are until 10, kitchen stops cooking by 9:15. I had them repeat it because I'd thought I heard incorrectly, but no, 45 mins before official closing time they no longer take orders. It's unfortunate as I really enjoyed both dine in and carry out, but am not certain I'll be coming back again. 6 min after 9:15, a full 39 minutes prior to "closing time..." Honestly, that's ridiculous< /review>

<name>Jessica Hunsanger</name><Rate>5</Rate><time>1532062590440<//time><Resp>None<//Resp><user_id>113531360780430414777< /user_id>< Text>
Thanks to all the previous reviews knowing the kitchen closes at 9:15 - I left a tad early for lunch (I work nights) and made it to Thai Specialty about 9:10pm to place a to-go order. It is clearly posted when you walk in that the kitchen closes at 9:15pm.
I’ve just finished what I can eat (already full) and the Pad See Ew is fantastic. I’ve eaten so much Pad See Ew over the years - finding good Thai places, bad ones, and making it myself - that I can usually tell quality by the smell. I wanted to dig into the bag on my way back to work it smelled so good.
I highly recommend giving this place a shot, it’s much better than any other options close to Brea.<//Text>

< Review>
Hidden gem of an outdoor swimming pool in the heart of the Mission district.
It's often pleasant weather with sun right there, during the foggy Summer months in SF.
Unfortunately the hours it's open (for lap swimming and for recreational swimming) are quite limited - I was told this is mostly because SF City doesn't want to pay the lifeguards who monitor it.  This seems weird to me as the City wastes so much money elsewhere, and there's an income stream from entrance fees to the pool ...<//Review>
